text: Doline (, ) is a village in Serbia. It is situated in the Kanjiža municipality, in the North Banat District, Vojvodina province. The village has a Hungarian ethnic majority (96.89%) and its population numbering 516 people (2002 census). Doline means sinkhole, though whether there is a connection is unclear. Karst topography, which was originally named in the Yugoslav-Italian area, includes sinkholes.Karst == References == ==See also== *List of places in Serbia *List of cities, towns and villages in Vojvodina Category:Places in Bačka
